From 78 K (liquid nitrogen temperature) to 350 K, the I-V characteristics of the device are characterized. The open-circuit voltage decreases linearly with temperature, shown in Fig. 4f, which is due to the effect of temperature on carrier diffusion. The photogenerated voltage depends on the built-in electric field, which relies on the contact potential difference, and it can be described as VD=k0TqlnNANDni2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
