				\begin{document}$$ {V}_D=\frac{k_0T}{q}\left\{\mathit{\ln}\frac{N_A\ {N}_D}{n_i^2}\right\} $$\end{document}. VD is the contact potential difference, K0 the Boltzmann constant, T the temperature, q the electron charge, NA the acceptor concentration, ND the donor concentration, and ni the intrinsic carrier concentration. With other parameters fixed, VD varies linearly with T, which is consistent with the experimental fitting results.
